articles.description: Arizona's Deandre Ayton became just the third player in Pac-12 history to be named both the conference's Player of the Year and Freshman of the Year.
articles.headline: Arizona's Deandre Ayton earns Pac-12's top player, freshman honors

articles.description: Last year, the Golden Flashes made a Cinderella run winning the MAC Tournament. In the opening round this year, Kent State finds the magic again on Kevin Zabo's game-winning shot.

articles.description: Cecil Williams had 18 points, six rebounds and six assists on Monday night and No. 8 seed Central Michigan dominated overtime for an 81-77 win over ninth-seeded Bowling Green in the first round of the Mid-American Conference Tournament.
articles.headline: Central Michigan powers past Bowling Green 81-77 in OT

articles.description: Kenny Carpenter scored 16 points, Anthony Wright added 12 and No. 8 seed Cleveland State upset No. 4 seed Oakland 44-43 in the Horizon League Tournament semifinals on Monday night.
articles.headline: Cleveland State upsets Oakland 44-43

videos.description: Dave Pasch and Bill Walton share their thoughts on the ongoing FBI investigation relating to Arizona and the NCAA.
videos.headline: Pasch, Walton share thoughts on investigation

videos.description: Arizona's Deandre Ayton converts his second bucket of the game on a midrange jumper, making him 2-for-2 to start the game.
videos.headline: Ayton drains midrange jumper

videos.description: Arizona's Keanu Pinder lays out for a loose ball and is unhappy after being hit in the head by Oregon's Abu Kigab.
videos.headline: Tempers flare in Eugene between Pinder, Kigab

videos.description: Arizona's Rawle Alkins gets the ball in the post and spins to convert a tough one-handed layup.
videos.headline: Alkins sinks tough lay-in for 3-point chance

videos.description: Oregon's Elijah Brown takes it to the paint and converts a tough layup to earn a trip to the line for a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Brown converts tricky layup for and-1 chance

videos.description: Deandre Ayton takes the ball up and finishes with a thunderous two-handed slam to ignite the Wildcats' bench.
videos.headline: Ayton throws down emphatic two-handed slam

videos.description: Oregon's Elijah Brown finds space from downtown and drains the deep 3-pointer late in the first half.
videos.headline: Brown displays range on long 3-pointer

videos.description: After missing two shot attempts on the possession, Arizona's Deandre Ayton fights for the rebound and sinks a tough layup to earn a trip to the line for a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Ayton cleans up misses with and-1 layup

videos.description: After grabbing the offensive rebound, Arizona's Deandre Ayton brushes off the contact and finishes a layup to earn the chance at a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Ayton converts layup for 3-point opportunity

videos.description: Arizona's Rawle Alkins drops a pass off to Deandre Ayton inside for an emphatic two-handed dunk.
videos.headline: Ayton rocks rim with thunderous two-handed slam

videos.description: Oregon's MiKyle McIntosh splits through the defense and converts a tough layup to earn a chance at a 3-point play.
videos.headline: McIntosh sinks and-1 layup

videos.description: Oregon's MiKyle McIntosh has some choice words for Keanu Pinder after Deandre Ayton and Elijah Brown get tangled up, and he is hit with the technical foul.
videos.headline: McIntosh accessed technical after Ayton, Brown scuffle

videos.description: Arizona's Rawle Alkins finds Deandre Ayton in the paint for a loud two-handed dunk.
videos.headline: Alkins sets up Ayton inside for two-handed slam

videos.description: After grabbing the steal, Oregon's Troy Brown goes coast-to-coast and soars for the one-handed slam.
videos.headline: Brown turns defense into quick offense

videos.description: With time running low in the second half, Arizona's Dylan Smith finds space behind the arc and converts the big 3-pointer to tie the game at 83.
videos.headline: Smith drains clutch 3-pointer to even game

videos.description: Arizona's Rawle Alkins hustles in transition and throws down a loud two-handed dunk. Following the emphatic finish, he gets in the face of Kenny Wooten and is hit with a technical foul.
videos.headline: Alkins accessed tech after breakaway slam
